BRIEFLY 
Digital Freezes Salaries: Digital Equipment Corp., facing a decline in 
earnings, said it will delay all salary increases for its 73,500 employees in 
the United States. The salary freeze will go into effect July 2, the beginning 
of Digital's fiscal year, and will be re-evaluated in late September or 
October, the company said. The Maynard, Mass.-based computer maker reported 
earnings in the quarter ending April 1 of $256.4 million, down from $305.1 
million a year earlier. 
